Morvin DUEL, Commissioner of Insurance, Etc., Plaintiff-Appellee, v. NATIONAL SURETY CORPORATION, Defendant-Appellant. No. 9025. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Oct. 24, 1946. J. G. Hardgrove, Paul R. Newcomb, and Bert Vandervelde, all of Milwaukee, Wis., (Miller, Mack & Fairchild, of Milwaukee, Wis., of counsel), for appellant. Frank T. Boesel, of Milwaukee, Wis., for appellee.

Before SPARKS and MAJOR, Circuit Judges, and BRIGGLE, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

By reference we adopt the opinion of the District Court as that of this court. See 64 F.Supp. 961.

Judgment affirmed.
